The first: 18th century, the introduction of steam power for the operation of production machines.
The second, beginning of the 20th century, electricity, chemistry, oil, mass production and assembly lines - Ford.
The third, early 70s: electronics, computers, the first robots, factory automation.
This fourth is instead substantially characterized by a connection between the physical system and the digital system.
